      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Construct stiffness QoI comparison — FEA vs bench (N=11)",
      "description": "FEA ensemble mean stiffness differed from experimental mean by 4.2% (E/uval = 0.87, acceptance threshold <1.96). All 11 constructs within ±10% band. A probabilistic UQ campaign (Latin Hypercube, 500 samples) was performed varying titanium elastic modulus ±5%, cortical bone modulus ±15%, and friction coefficient ±0.05; stiffness QoI showed low sensitivity to bone modulus variation and moderate sensitivity to friction, informing the final model parameter selections documented in the UQ report (Nagaraja et al. 2023, Appendix C).",
      "outcome": "Accepted",
      "quantitativeResult": "Mean error 4.2%; E/uval 0.87"
    },
    {
