      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum isotropic linear-elastic model with frictional contact at screw-block interfaces is appropriate for quasi-static compression-bending below yield; justified by literature and corroborated by validation agreement.",
      "rationale": "Titanium alloy Ti-6Al-4V modelled as isotropic linear elastic (E=114 GPa, ν=0.34) consistent with published material data. Frictional contact (μ=0.3) at all metal-on-metal and metal-on-UHMWPE interfaces. Model form appropriate for quasi-static loading below fracture. Agreement with N=11 bench tests corroborates form selection. Model form level 3 achieved."
