    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed required level. One factor (Test conditions) achieved level 2 against a required level 3; this shortfall is accepted given regulatory precedent for single-condition ASTM F1717 testing, the medium model risk classification, and the corroborating multi-laboratory experimental dataset (N=11). All three QoIs satisfy quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96; error < 10%). The FEA modeling framework is accepted as sufficiently credible to support the non-cannulated pedicle screw 510(k) submission.",
